    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: High prevalence of mental health issues in Brazil -> Goal: Inform & establish urgency -> Presentation: Large statistic cards -> Interaction: Static -> Justification: Immediate, high-impact communication of core data points.
        - Report Info: Uneven distribution of psychologists -> Goal: Show access disparity -> Viz: Donut Chart -> Interaction: Hover to see region data -> Justification: Excellent for showing proportions of a whole, visually highlighting the concentration in one region. Library: Chart.js/Canvas.
        - Report Info: Key areas for AI application (Diagnosis, Treatment, etc.) -> Goal: Organize & allow deep-dive -> Presentation: Interactive Tabbed Section -> Interaction: Click to reveal detailed text and impact summary -> Justification: Breaks down dense information into user-selected, manageable chunks, promoting active exploration over passive reading. Method: JS content switching.
        - Report Info: Ethical Pillars (New) -> Goal: Organize foundational rules -> Presentation: Grid of detailed cards -> Interaction: Hover for visual emphasis -> Justification: Clearly defines abstract concepts in a scannable format. Method: HTML/Tailwind.
        - Report Info: Operational and Regulatory challenges -> Goal: Inform on risks/compliance -> Presentation: Grid of info cards -> Interaction: Static with hover effect -> Justification: Presents distinct concepts clearly and concisely in a visually organized manner, allowing easy comparison. Method: HTML/Tailwind.
        - Report Info: The future collaborative model -> Goal: Conclude with a vision -> Presentation: Simple HTML/CSS diagram -> Interaction: Static -> Justification: A strong, clear visual metaphor to summarize the report's main thesis. Method: HTML/Tailwind.
    -->
